        "description": "Query historical protocol data for multiple protocols, metrics and assets.

The endpoint will create all possible triples **(protocol, metric, asset)** 
based on the supplied parameters. It will then exclude the triples for which 
there is no recorded/available data to export and it will compile a flat list 
of `Snapshot` objects for each of the remaining triples.

A `Series` object is serialised as:

```json
{
    "protocol": "maker",
    "metric": "borrow_apr",
    "asset": "dai",
    "points": [
      [123456789, "8.1234"],
      ...
    ]
}
```

The full response payload will include a list of `Series` objects, and each 
`Series` object will include a list of `Points`. A `Point` is a two element 
tuple, representing the timestamp and the value of each measurement.
